---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Framing - Design for the Continuum" activePage="framing">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-20">
    <h1 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] max-w-[1400px]">
      Recent eco-juridical moves (e.g., rights of nature, more-than-human councils) extend standing
      to non-human beings yet leave largely unexamined the formation of the representer.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Posit Statement -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <h2 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.2] max-w-[1400px]">
      I posit that before representation comes understanding and training representational subjectivity (even in a collective perspective).
    </h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Research Problem Section -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2">Research Problem</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-20">Research Question</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] opacity-20">Research Objectives</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-2/3 text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] lg:leading-[30px] font-semibold max-w-[800px]">
        <p class="mb-6">
          All living can be thought of as meeting (Buber) and when we are 
          dealing with representation of MOTH subjectivity, an attitude of 
          meeting the living as an intersubjective experience need necessarily 
          be adopted.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          This is obviously a poetic as well as a political, or poethical approach.
          In Native Hawaiian world-making, an element of the world—wind, 
          rock, ancestor, or place—is experienced as alive insofar as it 
          participates in, and is carried by, the ongoing creation of stories.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          From this epistemological perspective, moʻolelo (story) is not just 
          narrative but a living weave of relations.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          Reductionist mechanistic views are obsolete, we require ways of 
          engaging with the world that present possibilities for co existance.
          For this, it is important to explore the whole range of intersubjective 
          experiences, starting from the Ethics of care, which is about the 
          relationship of respect and commitment for what is radically
          foreign to us. A relationship experienced firsthand, in the cognitive 
          encounter "open and receptive" (p. 63) that makes experience the 
          starting point for the development of new vocabularies. Nature, in 
          fact, is not a given, but in the encounter, the subject experiences "a
          generative thinking that invents new paths for interpreting 
          experience"
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research Question Section -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-20">Research Problem</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2">Research Question</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] opacity-20">Research Objectives</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <!-- Research Questions Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- RQ1 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➀</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                In what ways can we re-enchant human rationality and relationality so that the threshold between the human and (super)natural forces is unlearned?
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- RQ2 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➁</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                What are the ways in which experiences can be designed, curated (and measured) to act as a catalyst for the unlearning of threshold and re-enchantment of human rationality and relationality?
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- RQ3 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➂</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                What kind of potentialities of engagement arise, after human re-enchantment, from queering the relationship with MOTH?
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research Objectives Section -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-20">Research Problem</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-20">Research Question</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1]">Research Objectives</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <!-- Research Objectives Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- RO1 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➀</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                To select and analyze practices coming from Mediterranean ancestral "continuum" communities, figuring out ways to learn how their effects and affects can be measured
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- RO2 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➁</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                To redesign and formulate approaches (ecopedagogy) training the perspectives of a designer.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- RO3 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➂</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                To generate functional outcomes (like new ideas for conservation, shifts in attitude or motives for stewardship) at the personal and collective level of engagement with MOTH.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Methodology Section - Dark Background -->
  <section class="bg-charcoal text-cream px-6 lg:px-24 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2">Methodology</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] opacity-30">Output</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <!-- Methodology Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- M1 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓜ➀</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold mb-4">
                "critical training in empathetic relational imagination"
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm lg:text-[18px] leading-[1.4] font-semibold opacity-80">
                1. training through gestures, dances, music coming from mediterranean ancestral "continuum" community (open to other convenings from more than design radical pedagogies and epistemologies)
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- M2 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓜ➁</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold mb-4">
                "against extinction of experience"
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm lg:text-[18px] leading-[1.4] font-semibold opacity-80">
                1. workshops in design institution inspired from practices studied (sub1)
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- M3 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓜ➂</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold mb-4">
                "venturing beyond the bifurcation of nature"
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm lg:text-[18px] leading-[1.4] font-semibold opacity-80">
                1. collaborate with related experiences of MOTH representation
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Output Section - Dark Background -->
  <section class="bg-charcoal text-cream px-6 lg:px-24 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-30">Methodology</h3>
        <h3 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] leading-[1.1]">Output</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <!-- Output Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- O1 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓞ➀</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                1.knowledge: i.e. new interrelation/connection and platform for a community and practice
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- O2 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓞ➁</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                reviewed goal and participation: connection and platform for a community and practice
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- O3 -->
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="pl-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">Ⓞ➂</h4>
              <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                : new interaction/ connection and platform for a community and practice
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

